column5: The rain started to let up late this morning, so I grabbed my gear, put on the the wetskins and decided to head out on the river for a few hours....I was a little pessimistic at first due to spring like water levels on the river from all the rain and also the discoloration of the water....but that quickly changed after 45min...  Not the biggest I've ever caught, but it was nice just to hold her in my arms and then see her swim off again to grow bigger!!    The Release............
Cool Steve Another beauty!!!  Congratulations Thanks for sharing Jacques
i wish i could be a musky master like you steve.  whats your secret?????????????????????????????????????????

Thanks Jacques and Kevin....  I'm heading back out in a few minutes for some night time action....walleye that is   ...well....maybe a cast here and there for a skie  Anytime boys...you know you're welcome to come out
Beautiful fish...very nice colors  Great to see her swim off to fight again.   Cheers  Craig
Man, Your musky are really clean looking there.
excellent, I have caught a Pike, largest maybe only 4lb only (little guy). Interested to know which line you are using (lb test?)  Thanks
Congrats Steve, you did good! Nice to see you out and about.

Thanks guys...  Roy, it's nice to be out and about again!!...it's been busy around the house and at work but I'm finally seeing the light at the end of the tunnel  .....I start vacation for 4 weeks starting August 14th and I'm going to make sure I make up for all the lost time!!

"Busy" isn't a bad thing. It makes you really appreciate any down time you can find. You have a great four weeks....when you deserve it, it's much easier to take.  I have one week left right now but it's one of those years where things are a little more difficult than normal. You have a great time during your holidays!
AAAAHHHHHHAAAAA! LOL.....so thats what a musky looks like...i keep trying to fish for them but.........  Great looking fish   thanks for posting.
very jealous!!!  I've only caught a couple 'skis out of stony, but they were not of much size...
agreed, no busted fins. Very nice!
